responseText: NSLOCTEXT("[70199B914E7E03A9706A1499CF20B1FD]", "A06EE3364DED35522E5DACB948EAA45C", "\"May I inquire,\" I said, motioning to the brass orrery in her hand, \"what that device has to do with it?\" She looked down at the device, then, with a sudden realization, pulled it to her chest and clutched it protectively as she slowly backed away from me. \"Just stay right there, now,\" she warned. \"Keep your distance!\" \"Huh? Hey, relax!\" I said. \"I\'d never try to.\" But she wasn\'t listening. \"Don\'t even think of trying to follow me, elf!\" \"I\'m half-elven, actually,\" I said, smiling warmly in an attempt to calm her fears. Suddenly filled with mistrust, the hunter backed away from me as she drew her bow and nocked an arrow. \"The Bodabodaga is not for you!\" she shouted. \"Hands off! And don\'t try to follow me, neither!\" She continued to back away, picking up speed until she melted into the shadows of the forest and vanished as quickly as she\'d appeared.")
